  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can you delete all photos from your iPhone?",
  "response": "To delete all photos from your iPhone, you can follow these steps:\n\n### Method 1: Using the Photos App\n1. **Open the Photos App**:\n   - Tap the \"Photos\" app on your iPhone.\n\n2. **Go to the Library**:\n   - Select \"Library\" at the bottom of the screen.\n\n3. **Select All Photos**:\n   - Tap \"Select\" in the upper-right corner, then swipe across the screen to select all photos.\n\n4. **Delete Photos**:\n   - Tap the trash bin icon and confirm by selecting \"Delete [X] Photos.\"\n\n5. **Empty Recently Deleted Folder**:\n   - Open the \"Albums\" tab and go to the \"Recently Deleted\" folder.\n   - Tap \"Select\" > \"Delete All\" to permanently remove the photos.\n\n---\n\n### Method 2: Using iCloud Photos\nIf your photos are synced with **iCloud**, you can delete them by turning off iCloud Photos or deleting them from iCloud:\n\n1. **Turn Off iCloud Photos**:\n   - Go to **Settings** > [Your Name] > **iCloud** > **Photos** and toggle off \"iCloud Photos.\"\n   - Choose \"Remove from iPhone\" to delete all photos stored on your device.\n\n2. **Delete Photos from iCloud**:\n   - Open **iCloud.com** on a browser, sign in, and go to **Photos**.\n   - Select and delete the photos, which will also remove them from your iPhone.\n\n---\n\n### Method 3: Using a Third-Party App\nYou can use apps like **iMazing** or **iExplorer** to manage and delete all photos from your iPhone.\n\n---\n\n### Important Notes:\n- **Backup First**: Make sure to back up your photos to iCloud, a computer, or an external drive before deleting them.\n- **Synced Photos**: If your photos are synced from a computer or another device, deleting them on your iPhone may not remove them from the source.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
